==Old English==
===Etymology===
From Germanic *''faþmaz'', from Indo-European ''*pet-''.  Cognate with Old Saxon ''[[faþmos]]'' ''plural'' (Dutch ''[[vadem]], [[vaam]]''), Old High German ''[[fadum]]'' (German ''[[Faden]]''), Old Norse ''[[faðmr]]'' (Swedish ''[[famn]]'').  The PIE root is also the source of Greek ''[[πεταννύναι]]'', Latin ''[[patere|patēre]]''.

